SUMMARY:No one is free until we are all free: Movie night under the stars
LOCATION:633 Beaumont (métro Acadie)
DESCRIPTION:2026-06-27 19:30:00\n\n633 Beaumont (métro Acadie)\n\nhttps:/
 /www.openstreetmap.org/node/11973025945\n\nNotes on the films and content 
 warnings:\nThe films will contain mentions of genocide and other potential
 ly challenging subject matters. We have screened the films and provided de
 tailed content warnings under each title.Agenda7:30pm: Social\nShare snack
 s and tea with other attendees in the indoor space of Brique par Brique. W
 e will host some light\, self-guided crafting activities.8:30pm: Introduct
 ion &amp\; short activity by QCP 20268:45pm: No Pride in Genocide QCP 2026
 .\nAn approximately one hour screening in the outdoor space of Brique par 
